  "text": "The prevalence of isolated calf vein thrombosis (ICVT) is 5 to 12% in symptomatic patients [CITATION_1] and asymptomatic ICVT may occurin 15% of patients after total hip and total knee arthroplasty (TKA) [CITATION_2] . However, treatment of ICVT is still controversial.",
